<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-01T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-01T16:00:00-05:00" n="1498" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1498">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">833.24/8–144: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-01T18:00:00-03:00">August 1,
                                    1944—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 1—5:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>739. PC<note n="37" xml:id="d1498fn37">Patrol vessel, submarine
                                chaser.</note> boat furnished Uruguay under lend-lease arrived
                            Montevideo yesterday after uneventful trip. Naval Attaché states
                            President going aboard this afternoon, Uruguayan authorities very
                            pleased, and officers and crew of vessel delighted with training and
                            treatment in United States.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>